[INSTRUCTIONS]

1.replace ./userspace/public/libs/cms_util/memory.c with hostTools/memleak/memory.c
comment "smd" in ./targets.fs/src/etc/profile
burn image and then disconnect with host PC

2. check networking configuration
   1)CPE lan ip MUST be: 192.168.0.1
   2)Host PC ip MUST be: 192.168.0.2
   
3. run memleak application
   $ cd hostTools/memleak
   $ ./memleak

4. reboot cpe and connect with host PC at the same time
   MUST use eth0 to connect host PC
   #linux-user-mdk &
   #ifconfig eth0 192.168.0.1 netmask 255.255.255.0 up
   #smd

5. begin your testing
   ...^-^...

For more informations in hostTools/memleak.
